A young man man sits behind a large wooden desk here.  He wars a sash of green across his chest and a name plate on his desk says 'Guard Captain Mullen'. Below it is a small metal plaque 'in Realm service for 3 years'.  He pours over a complete mess of files on the tabletop, glancing quickly from one to the other, and doesn't seem to notice you as you approach.  Finally, after an uncomfortable silence he looks up at you.
"Ahh! Neither of the Nobility nor Merchantry.  A welcome respite.  What can I do for you?"
"Hello again."
Who are you?
"Mullen.  Captain Mullen.  I am in command of the Realm forces in Alinea."  He gestures to the nameplate on his desk.
The Realm? What is that, exactly?
He tilts his head to the side, confused, then his eyes widen as if seeing you for the first time.

"Ah, Yes.  A Lark.  Not to worry, I can explain. The Realm is the military force of the Mainland here on Sadelica.  King Treyborn has declared the island as part of the Mainland Empire, but in truth, he does not provide us enough resources to truly enforce that decree."
So the Realm is the government here?

"Basically, yes.  But the fact of the matter is, we don't have all that much sway here on Sadelica.  Certain Nobles and Merchants have occupied the island with much more more agency than us.  And that's not even mentioning the Order of Magi..."

He gives a sheepish grin.  "Quite frankly, calling ourselves part of the Mainland Empire would do a disservice to its might and power.  Instead we call ourselves 'The Realm' and we try to keep the peace around here."
Nevermind, I'll be going now.
player.once()

"The Realm is the military force of the Mainland here on Sadelica.  The King has declared the island as part of the Mainland Empire, but in truth, he does not provide us enough resources to truly enforce that decree."
I've got some questions.
"Ask whatever you'd like."
Nevermind.
Let's speak of something else.
"Indeed."
true
It's hard to explain, but I'm looking for something, and all I have is a number: '9'.  Know anything?

"The number 9 huh?  Well, there are eight warehouses in Alinea, all owned by various members of the Merchantry or the Nobility.  There's actually a ninth though, but it's under disrepair and unavailable for use.   Maybe that's what you seek?"
There's a 9th warehouse in Alinea?
"Yes.  It's on the far east of town.  Locked though.  Nobody really knows who owns it.  Nobody's been over there for quite a long time."
Is there any way for me to get inside the ninth warehouse?

"I doubt it.  That warehouse hasn't been used in a long time.  Although you might have some luck talking to some of the Merchantry folks about it. They've been scoping out the place for a while now and might have more information than me."
Let's speak of something else.
"Indeed."
What can you tell me about these warehouses?

"Well, Alinea is a port, so it's advantageous for one to own a warehouse here.  Ships come in, sell there wares to merchants and those merchants store the goods in a warehouse.  Traders come along and take these goods to all other parts of Sadelica.  You can turn a tidy profit with a business like that.  All the warehouses here are owned by a member of the Merchantry."
What can you tell me of the Merchantry?

"The Merchantry is the collective union of merchants on Sadelica.  They realized that one merchant by themselves holds little power, but as a group, they have tremendous sway.  Quite often at odds with the Nobility."
What can you tell me of the Nobility?

"There are quite a few nobles from the Mainland Empire who have staked their claims on Sadelica.  Some have more power than others, but of course gossip travels.  They all talk to each other.  They all know who's who and what's what."
Is there anything I can do for the Realm?
Captain Mullen's raises an eyebrow.  "Well, if you're not opposed to some dangerous work... we have two significant problems.  One regarding Bandits, and one regarding Lady Blackrose"
player.get('nodes.od3u5s592')
What can you tell me about the Order of Magi?

He purses his lips.  "A group which believes that Sadelica is their salvation.  They experiment with the magic here, and often cause critical problems for us.  I'd rather not speak of them.  They give me a headache."
false && player.questInProgress('QUEST_AlineaBandits')
Let's talk about the Bandits.
"I'm all ears.  What can you tell me?"
player.startQuest('QUEST_AlineaBandits');
What can you tell me about Alinea?

"It's port town, though a small one.  Bigger ports can be found at the northern and southern ends of Sadelica, so this place isn't particularly strategic.  But still, it's the place closest to the hinterlands in the northwest of Sadelica, so that makes it somewhat important for getting supplies there."
Anyone I should be on the lookout for?
"Well, Lord Guildimarche is probably the biggest one, but he hasn't expanded his power out here to Alinea yet.  I'm sure you'll find some of his brown-nosers though."
"Other than that? I'm not sure.  My policy has always been to pay them as little attention as possible, until I can't avoid them anymore."
Okay, enough about the Nobility.
"Indeed."
Actually, nevermind.  Let's talk about something else.
"Indeed."
questStepEQ("QUEST_AlineaBandits", 1);
I've spoken to the bandits.  They have some demands.
"They do, do they?  What might those demands be?"

"There are some Bandits blocking the road north.  It's actually becoming a significant problem. There are quite a few of them, and I don't have enough soldiers here to show a big enough force to intimidate them to leave, so I'm forced to wait for reinforcements."  He grimaces. "Those are... potentially several days away."
And you think I could do this?
"I mean, yeah, it will be dangerous, but you don't have any allegiances here.  You're a third party.  They might not attack you on sight like they have been doing to my men."
How long have the Bandits been there?
"For almost a month, they've been attacking trade caravans going up there.  But they've only outright blocked the road for a week."
I guess I could go check it out, for a price.
"I'd never expect somebody to do that for free.  If you can get rid of the Bandits, then I'd be very much in your debt actually.  Trust me, I'll make it worth your while."
Apparently they are exiled Nobility. They want to be reinstated.
Captain Mullen whistles softly.  "Do they now?  That's, not going to go over well.  No not well at all."
Lady Blackrose wishes to conquer Alinea?

"A very high-up member of the Nobility has come to Alinea recently.  Her name is Lady Aldebeth Blackrose, and she's brought a rather sizable contingent of soldiers.  They're camped out just to the east of town.  Apparently she wants to build Alinea out into a haven for her house, but I'm not so sure she doesn't mean to conquer the place."

"If possible, I'd like to resolve this peacefully.  if somebody would go in as a liaison and talk to them, see if they have any demands, see if they can be reasoned with, then maybe I can negotiate some terms until my reinforcements come."
Tell me about the Bandits.
Tell me about Lady Blackrose.
false && player.questInProgress('QUEST_AlineaFindSpyRigby')
Lets talk about Lady Blackrose.
"If something isn't done about them soon, we might not be able to get supplies up north to the hinterlands, and that would spell disaster for any settlements there."
Actually, let's talk about something else.
player.once()
player.once()
"Perhaps conquer is too harsh.  But if Lady Blackrose were to *replace* the Realm garrisoned here with the forces she brought, then she would have an awful lot of say over the port."
Isn't that illegal?  Wouldn't the Realm take issue with that?"

"We would if we had enough power to contend with the Nobility, but... alas."  He spreads his hands sheepishly.  "Of course she hasn't actually done anything yet, so I can't even file a formal complaint."
"I've enlisted a spy into the Blackrose ranks.  Her name is Rigby.  I need somebody unaffiliated with me to take messages back and forth between her and I.  Interested?"
I suppose could help you, if you paid me.
"Yes yes, of course I'd pay you.  Per message.  One-way."
Sure, I'd love to lend aid to the Realm.

"You'll have to find Rigby in the Blackrose camp out to the east side of town.  For goodness sakes, don't ask around for here - that's too conspicuous - but if you spend enough time there I'm sure she'll approach you on her own.  She is quite sharp."
Actually, nevermind.  Let's talk about something else.
"Indeed."
"You have a message for me?"
questStepEQ("QUEST_AlineaSpyRigby", 1);
I found Rigby. She gave me a message for you.
He takes the sealed envelope, flips it open and reads the contents.  A frown creases on his forehead as he does so, and when he finishes he slowly puts the paper down on his desk.
"Unwelcome news."
Anything I can do to help?
Huh?
What do you mean?
"The only person with enough influence to do that around her is Lady Blackrose, and I'm wont to ask her for any favors."
I see.  Well it can't hurt to try, can it?
"I suppose not, but I don't want to be the one that does it."  He gives a you a pointed stare.
Fine, I'll as Lady Blackrose about this.  But you owe me.
"Of course, of course."  He reaches into his desk and throws you a bag of coins.  "For your effort."
player.completeQuestStep('QUEST_AlineaBandits', 3);
